.TH BINSUID 1 "July 2026" "binsuid 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
binsuid \- automatic SUID, capabilities and sudo privilege escalation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B binsuid
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBbinsuid\fR scans Linux systems for exploitable SUID binaries, dangerous file
capabilities, and sudo misconfigurations, then performs automatic privilege
escalation with built-in payloads. No manual command editing is required.
.PP
Intended for authorized penetration testing, CTF challenges, and security training.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-auto
Escalate the highest-priority vulnerable target automatically.
.TP
.B \-y, \-\-yes
Skip the confirmation prompt.
.TP
.B \-\-quick
Limit filesystem enumeration to common binary directories.
.TP
.B \-\-scan-only
Scan and list vulnerable targets without offering escalation.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Print machine-readable JSON output.
.TP
.B \-\-silent
Print a one-line summary only.
.TP
.B \-\-concise
Compact one-line-per-target listing.
.TP
.B \-\-no-color
Disable ANSI color output.
.TP
.B \-\-dry-run
Show escalation plan without executing.
.TP
.B \-\-skip-suid
Skip SUID enumeration.
.TP
.B \-\-skip-capabilities
Skip file capability enumeration.
.TP
.B \-\-scan-process-caps
Include process capability enumeration.
.TP
.B \-\-skip-sudo
Skip sudo rule enumeration.
.TP
.B \-\-sudo-interactive
Run \fBsudo \-l\fR with password prompt.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Show version information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive escalation:
.PP
.RS
binsuid
.RE
.PP
Fully automatic:
.PP
.RS
binsuid \-\-auto \-y
.RE
.PP
Scripting:
.PP
.RS
binsuid \-\-json \-\-scan-only
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I binsuid/data/gtfobins-api.json
Bundled GTFOBins API snapshot.
